\nfont-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif, Arial, sans-serif !important;\n}\n.ffb-id-48096qs2:before,\n.ffb-id-48096qs2:after,\n.ffb-id-48096qs2:hover,\n.ffb-id-48096qs2:focus,\n.ffb-id-48096qs2 *,\n.ffb-id-48096qs2 *:before,\n.ffb-id-48096qs2 *:after,\n.ffb-id-48096qs2 *:hover,\n.ffb-id-48096qs2 *:focus{ \nfont-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif, Arial, sans-serif !important;\n}\n.ffb-id-48098lal .divider-custom-line{ background-color:#c4c4c4}<\/style><script type=\"text\/javascript\"><\/script><section class=\"ffb-id-48098uq0 fg-section fg-text-dark\" id=\"intro\"><div class=\"fg-container container fg-container-large fg-container-lvl--1 \"><div class=\"fg-row row    \" ><div class=\"ffb-id-48098uq1 fg-col col-xs-12 col-md-12 fg-text-dark\"><h1 class=\"ffb-id-48098uq4 fg-heading text-center    fg-text-dark\">FRESH SPRING ROLL<\/h1><div class=\"ffb-id-48098uq5 fg-paragraph ff-richtext text-left    fg-text-dark\"><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\">&ldquo;Goi cuon&rdquo;, fresh spring roll, is a Vietnamese dish traditionally consisting of pork, prawn, vegetables, bun (rice vermicelli), and other ingredients wrapped in &ldquo;banh trang&rdquo; (commonly known as rice paper).<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\">Served at room temperature (or cooled) and not deep fried or cooked on the outside. Fresh spring roll is listed at number 30 on World&rsquo;s 50 Most Delicious Foods complied by CNN Go. These rolls are considered to be a very popular appetiser with all visitors to Vietnam.<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\">Concierge recommends: &ldquo;Goi cuon&rdquo; is available from street food, small restaurants to fine dining venues. Vegetarians also can enjoy this dish. They are easy to make at home with local ingredients, or enjoy through Room Service or on our Nineteen buffet.<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\">&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\">For more information, please call Concierge Desk via extension 20 or email: concierge@caravelle